
1. Mozambique has the only national flag with a modern weapon on it.
2. The island is home to the Chapel of Nossa Senhora de Baluarte. Built in 1522, it is 
believed to be the oldest European building in the southern hemisphere.
3. Mozambique takes its name from an offshore island of the same name which was apparently 
named after Mussa al-Bik, an influential Arab slave trader who set himself up as sultan on 
the island in the 15th century.
4. Mozambique is the only country in the Commonwealth never to have been part of the 
British Empire.
5. The official language of Mozambique is Portuguese
